The Inspector-General of the National Police Service Hillary Mutyambai on Tuesday announced a recruitment drive for police constables. In a statement, he said the exercise will be held on Thursday, March 24, 2022, from 0800hrs to 1700hrs, across the country. The applicants must be Kenyan citizens aged between 18 and 28 years and hold National Identity Cards. “Applicants must possess a minimum mean grade of D+ (D plus) and above in the Kenya Certificate of Secondary Education(KCSE) examination or its equivalent from an examination body recognized in Kenya,” the statement reads. They must also meet the qualifications of Chapter 6 of the constitution which highlights leadership and integrity. “The applicants must be physically and medically fit and should not have any criminal records or pending criminal charges,” he said. The Inspector-General has warned candidates against submitting false academic certificates and testimonies and engaging in corruption. “They shall be disqualified, arrested and prosecuted,” he said. The statement further states that the applicants recruited will be representing the gender, ethnicity and regional diversity of the Kenyan people. The application forms can be picked from any police stations, Sub County Administrative Police Commander offices, County Commissioner’s office or any Huduma Center.